 on the matter of pain. (ii) Despite this challenge, by focusing on the resemblance relations that hold across pains, we can generate scientific progress in explaining, predicting and treating pain. In doing so, the book aims to provide a clear conceptual basis for interdisciplinary communication and a useful heuristic for future research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 4aEliminativismus. 4aFamilienähnlichkeit. 4aSchmerz. 4aStarker Intentionalismus. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh  aChronic pain.  afamily resemblance.  ascientific eliminativism.  astrong intentionalism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831106884740 cprintz978311068837540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311068840540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110688405423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110688405.jpg  a978-3-11-065906-1  De Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCb2020  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Ebook Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069628-8  DG Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070482-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKA